# Frontend Rules

## Responsibility

Implement user-facing experiences that match Product + Specs.

## Preconditions

- Spec + relevant Architecture exist
- UX-critical flows have acceptance criteria

## Practice

- Prefer clarity and accessibility over decorative complexity
- Follow existing design system when one exists; do not invent a parallel UI kit casually
- Keep API contracts aligned with Specs/Architecture
- Avoid cards/dashboard clutter on branded marketing surfaces unless the product requires it

## Forbidden

- Shipping UI for unspecified behavior
- Hardcoding secrets or production URLs with credentials
- Duplicating shared logic that already belongs in `packages/` (once packages exist)
